project1.exmplars: The student has very little facial expression or the facial  expression does not fit the tableau. The student looks right at the audience or camera.
The student makes some attempt at showing what the character is feeling through facial expression. The focal point is somewhat appropriate for the scene.

The student exhibits an appropriate facial expression and focal point. The face shows some emotional expression, but the student has not made a bold, strong choice to show what the character is feeling.
The student exhibits a bold, strong facial expression with an appropriate focal point. The face clearly expresses what the character is feeling.

project2.exmplars: It is unclear what the student is saying;student mumbles lines or races through them. Tone does not match the character.
The student has some difficulty speaking with appropriate diction, pace, or volume; sometimes hard to understand what the character is saying. Student speaks in a monotone.
The student speaks with appropriate diction, pace and volume; the character can be heard and understood most of the time. The tone sometimes matches the character being portrayed.
The student speaks with clear diction, at an appropriate pace and volume; the character can easily be heard and understood. The tone matches the character being portrayed.

project3.exmplars: The students pose is unclear or difficult to view. Student detracts from the overall effect of the tableau.
The student exhibits a frozen pose. Choices about level or shape are only partially visible. Student shows some attempt at physical expression.
The student exhibits a frozen pose. Choices about  level and shape are visible. The pose lacks bold, strong choices for physical expression.
The student exhibits a bold, strong pose. Choices about level and body shape are effective. The student is clearly visible and the spacing is well balanced.

The student exhibits a bold, strong facial expression with an appropriate focal point. The face clearly expresses what the character wants or feels.
